      "content": "RICE is a good first step for a common sprain, but if you're in serious pain, it's a sign you need a proper medical assessment. While you can try the RICE method, you should definitely get your ankle checked out, especially if it feels like it might snap. For immediate relief, I recommend taking an over-the-counter anti-inflammatory like Ibuprofen, and if the swelling is intense, a quick trip to an urgent care is the best way to get it sorted out fast.",
